# 2. Object Properties and Methods

## Object Properties

Properties represent the characteristics or attributes of an object.

Example

```javascript
let employee = {
    name: "Rahul",
    salary: 50000
};
```

Properties are:

* name
* salary

---

## Object Methods

Methods are functions stored inside an object.

Example

```javascript
let person = {
    name: "Ritika",

    greet: function(){
        console.log("Welcome");
    }
};

person.greet();
```

---

## Built-in Object Methods

### Object.keys()

Returns all property names.

```javascript
Object.keys(student);
```

---

### Object.values()

Returns all property values.

```javascript
Object.values(student);
```

---

### Object.entries()

Returns key-value pairs.

```javascript
Object.entries(student);
```

---

### hasOwnProperty()

Checks whether a property exists.

```javascript
student.hasOwnProperty("name");
```

---

## Advantages

* Keeps related data together.
* Improves code organization.
* Makes objects reusable.

---

## Applications

* Managing application data.
* API development.
* Configuration objects.
* JSON handling.

